news.title: Agency for lab testing of Chintels Paradiso towers is likely to be chosen next week
news.para: In its preliminary report, the three-member committee from the civil engineering department of IIT-Delhi highlighted that deterioration of the structures happened “faster than expected”.

news.title: Cover our green areas with mesh on demolition day: Societies near Supertech twin towers
news.para: At a meeting with officials of the Noida authority, Supertech and Edifice Engineering, the agency entrusted with the demolition of twin towers Ceyane and Apex, representatives of Supertech Emerald Court and ATS Greens Village RWAs have raised this issue.

news.title: Noida authority begins razing 47 illegal shops, 20 studio units in Gardenia Gateway
news.para: The demolition drive in the group housing society will continue for a few more days as six authorised convenience shops fall in the middle of the illegal kiosks, officials said. Though some illegal shop owners tried to protest, the local police quickly stepped in to disperse them.

news.title: IL&FS' headquarters in Mumbai's BKC sold to Brookfield for Rs 1,080 crore
news.para: The iconic property was one of the first structures to come up in BKC, which is now the de facto Central Business District of the country’s commercial capital. The high-end office building with around 4.5 lakh sq ft of leasable area counts IBM, IDFC, The Carlyle Group, Avendus and Paypal among its list of key tenants.

news.title: Delink electricity fee from common area & other maintenance charges: HERC
news.para: In July 2020, resident Naresh Kumar Jindal filed a complaint to the consumer grievance redressal forum (CGRF) against non-compliance with the HERC single-point supply provisions by the RWA and the developer of the group housing society.

news.title: Noida: Mascot Soho Manorath homebuyers in insolvency battle
news.para: Homebuyers of Mascot Soho Manorath in Greater Noida said on Tuesday they have been waiting years for possession but the project had made little progress.

news.title: Transfer ownership of Hotel Ashok, Jharkhand urges Centre
news.para: The India Tourism Development Corporation (ITDC) on November 24, 2020 had signed an agreement with the Jharkhand Tourism Development Corporation (JTDC) to transfer its 51 per cent stake in the hotel for Rs 10 crore.

news.title: Vigilance team checks Ludhiana civic body papers as 57,000 buildings have no records
news.para: This team was formed by principal secretary local bodies department to check the inquiry report submitted by additional commissioner Rishipal Singh in which it was highlighted that there was no record of 57,000 buildings when comparison between building plan approval and new electricity connection was done.

news.title: BMC to take decision on Mumbai Metro One property tax dues
news.para: ​​​On March 24, BMC officials had reached Metro One properties to disconnect water lines, but agreed to give MMOPL, which runs the Versova-Andheri-Ghatkopar line, two more days for clearing the dues.

news.title: Varanasi civic body starts action against house tax defaulters
news.para: VMC municipal commissioner Pranay Singh said that after giving repeated opportunities to clear the house tax, a large number of building owners did not pay attention.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh REAT to have two shifts
news.para: Bench number one will hold the court from 1.30pm to 4pm and bench number two from 10.30am to 1pm.

news.title: Prime minister inaugurates 5.21 lakh PMAY houses in Madhya Pradesh
news.para: So far, 2.5 crore houses have been constructed under the PMAY scheme in the country, including two crore in rural areas, he said. Madhya Pradesh chief minister Shivraj Singh Chouhan participated in the programme from Chattarpur in the state.

news.title: Cost of construction up 10-12% year-on-year: Report
news.para: The cost of key materials like cement and steel have risen over 20% yearly as of March 2022. These constitute a predominant share in the total cost of construction. So far, developers have been cautious about increasing prices as the market was recovering from the aftermath of Covid-19.

news.title: Amazon India opens 8.3 lakh sq ft office space in Chennai
news.para: The new office space, occupying 18 floors in the building, will support around 6,000 employees. This is Amazon's fourth office in Tamil Nadu and takes total office area to over 21 lakh sq ft.

news.title: Nashik civic body aims to collect Rs 50 crore in property tax
news.para: The total target includes Rs 50 crore property tax collection and remaining Rs 10 crore through water tax. The civic chief set the target during the meeting of all department heads of the civic body.
